{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"coaching":[{"coaching":"State the concrete attestation evidence the [operator-attested] existing T5e mention in docs/plan-review-gate.md will require (a change id / vote outcome / timestamp), recorded on the ticket.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["f8805931c92cc3c19"],"move_id":"14","move_name":"state attestation evidence","subject":"existing T5e mention in docs/plan-review-gate.md"},{"coaching":"Pin down blocking_fp_proxy denominator and base-rate skew with a concrete worked example.","decision":"block","finding_refs":["f95c3ca451cbd9457"],"move_id":"6","move_name":"specification by example","subject":"blocking_fp_proxy denominator and base-rate skew"},{"coaching":"Plan how AC proving-command validity and completeness will be verified in-session — restate any deferred or unobservable success target as an observable proxy.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f607dd457c67f9209","fff8de3fc977041a9"],"move_id":"9","move_name":"plan the verification","subject":"AC proving-command validity and completeness"},{"coaching":"Run a quick pre-mortem on subprocess failure modes and error-handling policy: how could this plan fail?","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f8da0983234749e5c","fa85c7f5b78c51b8f"],"move_id":"3","move_name":"pre-mortem","subject":"subprocess failure modes and error-handling policy"},{"coaching":"Weigh at least one structural alternative for RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY coupling across non-package boundary.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f886294e4fb8a627a"],"move_id":"5","move_name":"weigh alternatives","subject":"RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY coupling across non-package boundary"},{"coaching":"Propagate the revision for runs/README.md update scope for new metrics file to the child tickets.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["fae1e8e010c935f2c"],"move_id":"11","move_name":"propagate to children","subject":"runs/README.md update scope for new metrics file"},{"coaching":"Generalize atomic-write convention across harness scripts across the rest of the work.","decision":"advisory","finding_refs":["f5abffdcef3627907"],"move_id":"12","move_name":"generalize the finding","subject":"atomic-write convention across harness scripts"}],"coverage":{"counts":{"advisory_overflow":0,"advisory_surfaced":1,"blocking":2,"dropped":17,"indeterminate":0},"det":{"P1":{"ac_items":5,"blocking":false,"clarity_score":7,"name":"readiness-shape","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P2":{"blocking":false,"name":"resolution","probed":6,"ran":true,"references":6,"resolved":2,"status":"pass","unresolved_or_abstained":4},"P3":{"blocking":false,"name":"package-existence","packages":0,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P4":{"ac_items":5,"blocking":false,"desc_chars":8487,"file_impact":2,"name":"oversize","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P5":{"blocking":false,"children":0,"name":"task-dag","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P6":{"ac_items":5,"blocking":false,"name":"ac-quality","ran":true,"status":"fail","verify_commands_linted":66,"verify_lint_abstained":65},"P7":{"blocking":false,"destructive_hits":[],"name":"destructive-sniff","ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P8":{"blocking":false,"budget_tokens":868000,"name":"reviewability","plan_tokens":2139,"ran":true,"status":"pass"},"P9":{"applicable":true,"blocking":false,"file_impact":2,"name":"file-impact-coverage","ran":true,"status":"pass"}},"floored_criteria":["E6","F1","G1G2","T1","T5b","T5e","T8"],"floored_finding_ids":["fff8de3fc977041a9","f8da0983234749e5c","fa85c7f5b78c51b8f","f886294e4fb8a627a","fae1e8e010c935f2c","f5abffdcef3627907"],"llm_ran":true,"metrics":{"claim_path":"no-llm/no-network (structural; the fast claim check is a local HMAC verify)","det_ms":233.2,"llm_calls":28,"llm_ms":813238.4,"total_ms":813607.9,"verify_requests":26},"narrowed":true,"remediation":{"baseline":"sidecar","eligible":true,"reasons":{"code_unchanged":true,"plan_changed":true,"registry_unchanged":true,"sidecar_baseline":true,"within_window":true}},"routing":{"agent_tier":["A1","E4","G1G2","G6","G7","T1","T10","T11","T13","T14","T3","T5c","T8","removal-rationale"],"single_turn":["COH","E1","E2","E3","E5","E6","F1","G5","T2","T4","T5b","T5e","T6","T7","T9","hedge"]}},"findings":[{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Strengthen AC4's proving command to grep for a phrase unique to the new alarm/demotion section (e.g., `grep -q '10%' docs/plan-review-gate.md`) rather than 'T5e' which already appears in the pre-existing calibration table.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["docs/plan-review-gate.md line 142 already contains: 'demoted **T5e to advisory**'","AC4 proving command: 'grep -q \"T5e\" docs/plan-review-gate.md'","grep -q on the current file would exit 0 with zero changes to the file"],"finding":"The AC4 proving command `grep -q 'T5e' docs/plan-review-gate.md` already passes on the current file (T5e is mentioned at line 142 in the calibration table) without any edit from this ticket — so the command cannot verify that the *new* alarm/demotion playbook content citing T5e demotion precedent was actually added.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8805931c92cc3c19","impact":1.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria AC4 / docs/plan-review-gate.md","norm_id":"ncf4424636af4eba5","priority":0.875,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["An implementer adds the alarm/demotion section but accidentally omits the T5e citation — the AC still passes on the pre-existing line 142 mention.","An implementer ships the ticket with no change to plan-review-gate.md at all — AC4's grep still exits 0."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Replace the T5e grep with a phrase that only appears in the new content, e.g.: `grep -q 'blocking_fp_proxy' docs/plan-review-gate.md && grep -q 'T5e' docs/plan-review-gate.md`","tier":"LLM","validity":0.875,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"broken_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Fix the `blocking_fp_proxy` formula: replace the three-way disjunction `force_close OR reopen_count>0 OR (no adverse post-claim edit)` with a proxy that is true only when there is affirmative evidence the block was unwarranted (e.g. `force_close OR reopen_count>0`, or `force_close OR (reopen_count>0 AND no adverse post-claim edit)`) — and document the intended semantics explicitly in the README and the metrics AC.","cohort":["G6"],"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"block","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Corpus inspection: of 628 rows in runs/outcome_corpus.jsonl, the overwhelming majority have post_claim_edit_class='none', reopen_count=0, force_close=false — meaning the third disjunct 'no adverse post-claim edit' evaluates to true for nearly all tickets.","The three conditions are connected with OR: a blocking finding is counted as a FP-proxy if ANY ONE of the three is true. Since 'no adverse post-claim edit' is the normal-case default, the OR short-circuits on condition 3 for ~95%+ of tickets.","A ticket where a plan gate correctly blocked a real issue, the author fixed it (no post-claim edit needed, no reopen, no force-close) would score as a FP under this formula — inverting the intended signal.","The intended proxy appears to be catching cases where the gate's blocking verdict was circumvented or unnecessary, but the formula as written catches nearly all normal resolved tickets."],"finding":"The `blocking_fp_proxy` formula's third disjunct — `(no adverse post-claim edit)` — is true for ~95%+ of corpus rows (the overwhelming majority have `post_claim_edit_class: 'none'`), making the entire `force_close OR reopen_count>0 OR (no adverse post-claim edit)` disjunction fire on virtually every blocking finding regardless of criterion quality. The metric would report near-100% FP-proxy for every criterion and be useless as a monitoring signal.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f95c3ca451cbd9457","impact":0.85,"is_primary":null,"location":"## What — Per-criterion trailing metrics section: 'blocking_fp_proxy(C) = (# of C's blocking findings whose ticket was subsequently adjudicated not-block-worthy — proxied by `force_close OR reopen_count>0 OR (no adverse post-claim edit)`)'","norm_id":"n6152034bbb71d0d4","priority":0.6375,"reason":"high-priority+criterion-opted-in","scenarios":["A criterion with 0 real FPs (every block was legitimate) would show ~95%+ blocking_fp_proxy, triggering the >10% alarm and a spurious demotion to advisory.","The demotion playbook fires on a permanently-inflated metric, making the entire monitoring pipeline a no-op from day one."],"severity":"critical","suggested_fix":"Redefine the proxy as `force_close OR reopen_count>0` (operational signals that the author had to work around the block), with 'no adverse post-claim edit' used as a *separate* `advisory_hit_rate`-style metric rather than folded into the FP proxy disjunction. If 'no adverse post-claim edit' is intended to mean 'the author didn't change anything, so the block may have been unnecessary,' it should be scoped to tickets where a review actually produced a blocking finding AND the ticket was closed without any author-side edit — expressed as a conjunction, not a disjunction: `(no adverse post-claim edit) AND (reopen_count == 0) AND (not force_close)` interpreted as 'ticket closed clean despite block' which would then be a separate metric track, not part of the FP proxy.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"yes"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"medium","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"medium","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"medium"}}},{"block_threshold":null,"blocking_enabled":null,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["P6"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["vague/subjective terms present: clean"],"finding":"Acceptance-criteria / definition-of-done quality issues.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f607dd457c67f9209","impact":0.4,"is_primary":null,"location":"","norm_id":"ned06ebc801a522e3","priority":0.4,"reason":null,"scenarios":[],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Split compound criteria, replace subjective terms with observable outcomes, and state how each is verified.","tier":"DET","validity":1.0,"verification":null},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Document the `post_claim_edit_class` enum as a shared contract in README.md (listing all currently valid values and their adverse/non-adverse classification) so any future miner extension has a documented change-surface and the harness can be updated intentionally.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["'adverse post-claim edit … is defined once: post_claim_edit_class ∈ {\"plan-authored-post-claim\", \"ac-strengthened\", \"substantive-unclassified\"}'","The miner (mine_outcome_corpus.py) produces post_claim_edit_class — if it gains new classes, the harness is not updated automatically","No interface/contract document ties the harness's adverse-set to the miner's enum"],"finding":"The `adverse post_claim_edit_class` set (`{\"plan-authored-post-claim\", \"ac-strengthened\", \"substantive-unclassified\"}`) is a business rule defined in the harness that mirrors a classification produced by `mine_outcome_corpus.py`. The plan does not document this as a contract point or specify what happens if the miner adds a new edit-class — the harness would silently treat a new substantive class as non-adverse, corrupting blocking_fp_proxy.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6f1a0ef4e1023cf7","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'adverse post-claim edit' definition; `gate_eval_instrumentation.py`","norm_id":"nb01be1706e2adc6c","priority":0.1237,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A future miner update adds a new edit class (e.g., 'scope-reduced') representing substantive author backtracking; the harness silently treats all such tickets as non-adverse, inflating advisory_application_rate false negatives."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add an assertion in the harness: `KNOWN_CLASSES = {\"none\",\"cosmetic\",\"operator-attested-retag\",\"plan-authored-post-claim\",\"ac-strengthened\",\"substantive-unclassified\"}; assert set(corpus_df.post_claim_edit_class.unique()).issubset(KNOWN_CLASSES), f'Unknown edit classes: {unknowns}'` — this turns a silent divergence into a loud failure.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify that `--emit` writes `gate_eval_metrics.json` atomically (write to a `.tmp` sibling file, then `os.replace()`) to prevent partial-write corruption and make concurrent invocations safe.","cohort":["T5b","T6","T9"],"criteria":["T5b","T9"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["AC states '--emit writes per-criterion metrics to …gate_eval_metrics.json' with no mention of atomic write pattern (write-to-temp + rename)","No locking or idempotency guarantee is described for concurrent --emit invocations","T5b checklist: 'writes are idempotent; partial state is safe/durable'"],"finding":"The `--emit` write to `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json` is not specified as atomic: a concurrent or interrupted invocation could leave a partially-written JSON file that corrupts subsequent reads or CI assertions.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fb6850fd489b61b5e","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — second AC bullet; Scope section — gate_eval_instrumentation.py","norm_id":"n887d6ae8976d5e22","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Two CI jobs run --emit simultaneously (e.g., parallel test shards); both write to the same path, interleaving bytes and producing invalid JSON","A run is interrupted mid-write; the next CI assertion (`python -c … assert d and any(…)`) fails on a truncated file"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Write to `gate_eval_metrics.json.tmp`, flush, then `os.replace('gate_eval_metrics.json.tmp', 'gate_eval_metrics.json')` — this is atomic on POSIX and safe on Windows with Python 3.3+.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.25,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Document (in the plan or harness docstring) that concurrent live-refresh invocations are not supported and that CI should use `--no-refresh`; or specify a file-lock around the miner subprocess call to serialize concurrent refreshes.","cohort":["T5b","T6","T9"],"criteria":["T9"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan says miner 'atomically writes runs/outcome_corpus.jsonl' but does not address two simultaneous callers both spawning the miner","No file lock or sentinel is mentioned to serialize concurrent refreshes","T9 checklist: 'shared/mutable state mutated atomically … no check-then-act TOCTOU'"],"finding":"Two concurrent gate_eval invocations without `--no-refresh` will both launch the miner subprocess simultaneously, racing on the `runs/outcome_corpus.jsonl` write; even though the miner itself writes atomically, two simultaneous miner processes may produce interleaved intermediate state or double-compute without the job being aware.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f26ac997e1ad70757","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Corpus acquisition (subprocess, not import)'","norm_id":"n0e315b03680d17e4","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["Parallel CI matrix jobs both invoke gate_eval without --no-refresh; both spawn miner; one miner's atomic rename races with the other's, leaving a valid but potentially wrong-generation corpus for one of the readers"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a note in the Scope/AC section: 'Concurrent --refresh invocations are not safe; CI MUST use --no-refresh. Local ad-hoc runs serialize naturally.' This documents the constraint without adding locking complexity.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"insufficient","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Resolve the blocking-FP-proxy substrate conflict: either update the parent epic's Success Criteria to drop the 'against E1's committed finding-adjudication ground-truth corpus' clause (reflecting E1's descoping) before this leaf is re-reviewed, or add a documented rationale in the leaf explaining why the outcome-corpus proxy is a valid substitute and reference the parent AC update.","cohort":["G7"],"criteria":["G7"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Parent SC: 'blocking-FP proxy … measured by R7's instrumentation against E1's committed finding-adjudication ground-truth corpus; 10% is the demotion threshold'","Leaf plan: 'blocking_fp_proxy(C) = (# of C's blocking findings whose ticket was subsequently adjudicated not-block-worthy — proxied by `force_close OR reopen_count>0 OR (no adverse post-claim edit)`) / (total # of C's blocking findings)'","E1 outcome comment confirms the adjudication corpus was 'INVALIDATED … and DESCOPED' — but that comment was added after the parent's plan-review was signed; the parent's signed SC still names the corpus as authoritative","Per CONFLICT RULE: the parent SC wins; the leaf's substitution of a different proxy signal is a redefinition, not a narrowing"],"finding":"The leaf redefines the blocking-FP-proxy measurement substrate in a way that contradicts the parent's signed Success Criterion. The parent specifies the metric is 'measured by R7's instrumentation against E1's committed finding-adjudication ground-truth corpus'; the leaf drops that corpus entirely and substitutes outcome-corpus proxy signals (force_close / reopen_count / adverse post-claim edit), making the two definitions measure different things under the same name.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f4f91ab070a24fb4e","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Parent epic Success Criteria ('measured by R7's instrumentation against E1's committed finding-adjudication ground-truth corpus'); Leaf plan 'What' section, blocking_fp_proxy(C) definition","norm_id":"nbe6e2862f041a45e","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["A downstream reviewer checking the leaf against the parent's SC will find the blocking-FP-proxy definition contradicts the parent — even if the E1 descoping was valid, the parent AC was never updated to reflect it.","If the parent is later amended to remove the E1-corpus reference, the leaf becomes clean; until then the leaf diverges."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Update the parent epic (`pastoral-aquatic-viper`) Success Criteria to replace 'measured by R7's instrumentation against E1's committed finding-adjudication ground-truth corpus' with 'measured by R7's instrumentation using outcome-corpus proxy signals (force_close, reopen_count, adverse post-claim edit class), as E1's finding-adjudication corpus was descoped (see E1 outcome comment).' This re-stales the parent's plan-review attestation; re-review the parent, then re-review this leaf against the corrected parent.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.3571,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"insufficient","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"insufficient","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add to the plan (in the `has_strong_finding` definition): specify the exact provenance of the `severity` string field in sidecar findings — which pass sets it, what the full closed vocabulary is (e.g., `{\"critical\",\"major\",\"minor\",\"low\"}`), and how it is derived from verifier axes — so the predicate is unambiguously implementable.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'has_strong_finding (the exact \"substantive advisory\" predicate): ∃ a surfaced sidecar finding with decision ∈ {\"block\",\"advisory\"} AND priority >= 0.5 AND severity ∈ {\"critical\",\"major\"}'","plan_review_finder.md:21: 'Do NOT emit severity, confidence, or priority — a separate pass computes those.'","sidecar.py:430: '\"severity\": f.get(\"severity\")' — the field is persisted but its origin is never defined in the plan","adjudication_corpus.jsonl row 1: shows 'severity': 'major' and row 3: 'severity': 'minor' — confirming two values exist in practice, but the full enum and derivation rule are absent from the plan"],"finding":"The `has_strong_finding` predicate requires `severity ∈ {\"critical\",\"major\"}`, but the plan never defines how the `severity` string field originates in plan-review sidecar findings. The Pass-1 finder prompt explicitly states 'Do NOT emit severity' (plan_review_finder.md:21), and the Pass-2 verifier emits ordinal axes (`prod_impact`, `debt_impact`, `blast_radius`, `likelihood`, `reversibility`) — not a rolled-up severity string. The adjudication corpus shows findings carry `severity: \"major\"`/`\"minor\"` but the derivation rule (what mapping converts verifier axes to this label) is absent from the plan. An implementer cannot write `has_strong_finding` without resolving where this field comes from.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fcbf676c9cd766792","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'Outcome classifier' — has_strong_finding predicate definition","norm_id":"n8b40dd3d0dc7470d","priority":0.099,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementer building `has_strong_finding` reads the sidecar's `severity` field and needs to know whether it is set by the finder, the verifier, decide.py, or some other step — and what the full vocabulary is. Without this, they may apply the predicate to a field that contains unexpected values (e.g., 'minor', None, or a verifier-axis composite) and silently misclassify all frozen cases.","If `severity` is None for many findings (the finder does not emit it), the predicate would incorrectly exclude findings that should be strong, producing a systematically wrong `has_strong_finding` for the 8 frozen cases."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Reconcile the plan's 'adverse post-claim edit' definition with the miner's `_SUBSTANTIVE_CLASSES`: explicitly state whether `operator-attested-retag`, `premise-invalidated`, `scope-reduction`, and `approach-change` are adverse (and therefore make a blocking finding NOT an FP in `blocking_fp_proxy`) or not adverse — and document why the classifier's C1 treatment of `operator-attested-retag` as CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED is consistent with excluding it from the 'adverse' metric vocabulary.","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":["Plan: 'adverse post-claim edit (used by both the classifier gate and the metrics below) is defined once: post_claim_edit_class ∈ {\"plan-authored-post-claim\", \"ac-strengthened\", \"substantive-unclassified\"}'","mine_outcome_corpus.py:419-427: _SUBSTANTIVE_CLASSES includes 'operator-attested-retag', 'premise-invalidated', 'scope-reduction', 'approach-change', 'ac-strengthened', 'plan-authored-post-claim', 'substantive-unclassified' (7 values)","Plan: 'C1 post_claim_edit_class == \"operator-attested-retag\" → CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED' — treating operator-attested-retag as an adverse outcome","outcome_corpus.jsonl row 40 (115b-ceea): post_claim_edit_class=operator-attested-retag — a CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED case that is adverse by the classifier but excluded from the 'adverse' metric vocabulary"],"finding":"The plan's 'adverse post-claim edit' definition (used by both the classifier gate and `blocking_fp_proxy`) enumerates only three classes: `{\"plan-authored-post-claim\", \"ac-strengthened\", \"substantive-unclassified\"}`. But the miner's `_SUBSTANTIVE_CLASSES` set (mine_outcome_corpus.py:419-427) contains seven classes including `\"operator-attested-retag\"`, `\"premise-invalidated\"`, `\"scope-reduction\"`, and `\"approach-change\"` — four classes that appear in the corpus (e.g., `operator-attested-retag` at corpus rows 40, 54, 63) but are absent from the plan's 'adverse' vocabulary without explanation. An implementer computing `blocking_fp_proxy`'s 'not-block-worthy' condition encounters a decision point: are tickets with `operator-attested-retag` or `premise-invalidated` adverse (making the ticket NOT an FP) or not adverse (making it an FP)? The plan's own cascade puts `operator-attested-retag` in CAUGHT-BUT-IGNORED (C1), implying it IS adverse — yet the `blocking_fp_proxy` definition excludes it from 'adverse'.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f17f3564f228d883d","impact":0.33,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'Per-criterion trailing metrics' — blocking_fp_proxy definition and 'adverse post-claim edit' definition","norm_id":"n27fcfc350270eeb0","priority":0.1237,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":["An implementer computing `blocking_fp_proxy` for a ticket where the blocking finding preceded an `operator-attested-retag` edit cannot determine if this counts as 'adverse' (not an FP) or 'not adverse' (an FP), because the plan's stated adverse vocabulary excludes operator-attested-retag but the classifier treats it as an adverse outcome.","If the implementation uses _SUBSTANTIVE_CLASSES directly (the natural reuse from the existing miner), the metric will count operator-attested-retag tickets as having an adverse edit, underreporting the FP rate."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Since C1 treats operator-attested-retag as a legitimate catch (the gate functioned correctly), it should be included in 'adverse' for the blocking_fp_proxy formula too. Revise: 'adverse post-claim edit: post_claim_edit_class ∈ {\"plan-authored-post-claim\", \"operator-attested-retag\", \"ac-strengthened\", \"substantive-unclassified\"} (all substantive non-cosmetic classes that indicate the gate's concern was warranted).'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.375,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"low","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.75,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E4"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"`mine_outcome_corpus.build_corpus()` calls `sys.exit()` on floor-check failure (mine_outcome_corpus.py:381), not `raise SystemExit` or a domain exception. The plan asserts the new job 'imports `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module and calling its build entry,' but calling `sys.exit()` from within an imported module terminates the calling process (`gate_eval_instrumentation.py`) rather than propagating a catchable exception. The harnesses directory also has no `__init__.py`, so the import requires path manipulation. No existing harness currently imports `mine_outcome_corpus`.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f163868557e70ce81","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'rebuilds the outcome corpus from live store history by importing `mine_outcome_corpus` as a module'; mine_outcome_corpus.py:381","norm_id":"nb3950aeb50a36178","priority":0.0,"reason":"low-validity","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add to the Scope section: 'The harness imports `mine_outcome_corpus` via `importlib.util.spec_from_file_location`; floor-check failure from `build_corpus()` propagates as `SystemExit` and should be caught and re-raised as a descriptive `RuntimeError` so `--verify-repro` produces a clear diagnostic rather than a silent exit.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.1667,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"na","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["G6"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The `--window N` 'most-recent N reviews' ordering is mechanistically underspecified: the outcome corpus schema (as produced by `build_corpus()`) contains no timestamp field, so 'most-recent N' has no resolvable ordering criterion across tickets. The AC requires `--window N` to yield a strict subset, but without a cross-ticket sort key the implementer must guess (e.g., alphabetical by ticket_id, or by sidecar file timestamp read separately) — two implementers could produce different subsets.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f5bb27ae5114b9bab","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — per-criterion trailing metrics definition; AC: '`--window N` bounds the trailing window and is exercised by the golden test (a smaller N yields a subset)'","norm_id":"n383f4ff86087d0ee","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a `latest_review_ts_ns` column to `build_corpus()` / `build_row()` (taken from the most-recent REVIEW_RESULT blob timestamp in the git-walk event store, already available in the blobs as `ts`). The gate-eval job then sorts by this column descending and takes the first N rows. Document this in the Scope section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The blocking_fp_proxy denominator uses the phrase 'no corresponding adverse post-claim edit' but never defines which post_claim_edit_class values count as 'adverse'. The miner's closed vocabulary has 6 values (plan-authored-post-claim, operator-attested-retag, ac-strengthened, substantive-unclassified, cosmetic, none). An implementer must decide: does 'adverse' mean any non-'none', or only substantive classes (excluding 'cosmetic'), or only the 3 classes also used in §5.2's substantive set? The plan's metric definition section is missing this co-located decision rule.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f6668a518d13cf6a5","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Per-criterion trailing metrics', blocking-FP proxy(C) definition","norm_id":"n3bd8a447e0d4b3f4","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"In the 'blocking-FP proxy(C)' bullet, replace 'no corresponding adverse post-claim edit' with 'post_claim_edit_class ∈ {\"none\", \"cosmetic\"}' (i.e., no substantive post-claim edit) — mirroring the _SUBSTANTIVE_CLASSES set already used by the miner.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The '--window N bounds the trailing window' feature is specified as 'most-recent N reviews, default N=200', but the outcome corpus schema (ticket_id, ticket_type, level, post_claim_edit_class, reopen_count, force_close, completion_verifier_fail_count, review_round_count, had_persisted_review) contains no timestamp field. The plan gives no specification of the sort key that defines 'most-recent', leaving the windowing algorithm mechanistically undefined.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f900ad6d63ff66c12","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Per-criterion trailing metrics (over the most-recent N reviews, default N=200)'; AC — '--window N bounds the trailing window'","norm_id":"n82be180fffb2b848","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:absence-refuted","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"no","cited_reference_accurate":"na","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"","cohort":null,"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"dropped","drop_reason":null,"evidence":[],"finding":"The `--emit` proving command only asserts the presence of `blocking_fp_proxy` but the AC text explicitly requires three fields — `advisory_application_rate`, `blocking_fp_proxy`, AND sample counts — all be present and non-null; an implementation that omits `advisory_application_rate` or sample counts would still pass the proving command.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f02110bbe68e27a7e","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — `--emit` AC proving command: `python -c \"import json;d=json.load(open('...'));assert d and any('blocking_fp_proxy' in v for v in d.values())\"`","norm_id":"ne8559e55700069e1","priority":0.0,"reason":"veto:cited-reference-inaccurate","scenarios":[],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Replace the single-field check with: `python -c \"import json; d=json.load(open('docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json')); assert d and any('blocking_fp_proxy' in v and 'advisory_application_rate' in v for v in d.values()), 'missing required metric fields'\"`","tier":"LLM","validity":0.2857,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"no","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"no","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"na","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"no","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.6,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Replace the `...` ellipsis in the AC2 proving command with the full path: `python docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/gate_eval_instrumentation.py --emit && python -c \"import json; d=json.load(open('docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json')); assert d and any(all(k in v for k in ('blocking_fp_proxy','advisory_application_rate','sample_counts')) for v in d.values())\"`","cohort":["E2","E6","F1"],"criteria":["E6","F1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Plan text: `python .../gate_eval_instrumentation.py --emit && python -c \"import json;d=json.load(open('docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json'))...\"` — the `...` before `/gate_eval_instrumentation.py` is not an expandable shell path; the full path `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/gate_eval_instrumentation.py` is established elsewhere in the plan but not substituted here.","Defect taxonomy item 3 (wrong helper-script argv / path): the command references a non-resolvable path segment."],"finding":"The proving command in AC2 uses a literal `...` ellipsis (`python .../gate_eval_instrumentation.py --emit`) that is not a valid shell path and will fail if executed verbatim by an agent.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fff8de3fc977041a9","impact":0.44,"is_primary":null,"location":"Acceptance Criteria — second bullet (`--emit` AC), proving command string","norm_id":"nef2ca2ff6d3baddf","priority":0.22,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["An executing agent copies the proving command verbatim and gets `python: can't open file '.../gate_eval_instrumentation.py': [Errno 2] No such file or directory`, making the AC unverifiable in-session.","CI automation that uses the proving command from the plan ticket would silently fail at the shell expansion step."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"python docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/gate_eval_instrumentation.py --emit && python -c \"import json; d=json.load(open('docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json')); assert d and any(all(k in v for k in ('blocking_fp_proxy','advisory_application_rate','sample_counts')) for v in d.values())\"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.5,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"na","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"no","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"no","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"underspecified_oracle","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Specify that the gate_eval job checks the subprocess return code and stderr, surfaces a clear error (non-zero exit + message) on miner failure, and documents whether it falls back to the last committed corpus or aborts.","cohort":["T5b","T6","T9"],"criteria":["T5b"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Plan states 'invokes mine_outcome_corpus.py as a subprocess … atomically writes runs/outcome_corpus.jsonl, then reads that JSONL' with no mention of checking subprocess return code or stderr","'--no-refresh flag skips regeneration' — fallback exists for CI but not for live-run failures","mine_outcome_corpus.py 'calls sys.exit() on floor-check failure' — non-zero exit is an expected failure mode, yet no handling is prescribed"],"finding":"The subprocess invocation of `mine_outcome_corpus.py` has no specified error-handling: if the subprocess exits non-zero (e.g., floor-check failure, missing data, I/O error), the plan does not state whether the job aborts with a clear diagnostic, falls back to the committed corpus, or silently proceeds with a stale/empty corpus.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f8da0983234749e5c","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — 'Corpus acquisition (subprocess, not import)'","norm_id":"n642cba19d06dcde9","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Corpus data becomes unavailable mid-run (network, missing git history); subprocess exits non-zero; gate_eval silently reads a stale corpus or crashes with an unhandled exception","CI pipeline without --no-refresh fails the miner floor-check; the instrumentation job swallows the error and emits misleading metrics"],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"After the subprocess call, assert `proc.returncode == 0`, log stderr on failure, and either raise a descriptive RuntimeError or, if fallback to committed corpus is desired, document that path explicitly and log a WARNING that metrics reflect stale data.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add to the 'Corpus acquisition' section: specify the harness behavior on subprocess non-zero exit — e.g., 'if the subprocess returns non-zero, the harness prints stderr, exits non-zero (propagates), unless --no-refresh is also passed in which case it reads the committed corpus as fallback.'","cohort":["T8"],"criteria":["T8"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["Plan: 'The job refreshes the outcome corpus by invoking mine_outcome_corpus.py as a subprocess... then reads that JSONL. It does NOT import and call build_corpus(), because that entry calls sys.exit() on floor-check failure (mine_outcome_corpus.py:381)'","Plan: 'A --no-refresh flag skips regeneration and reads the committed corpus (offline / CI use)'","ABSENCE: No fallback or error-handling protocol specified for subprocess non-zero exit"],"finding":"The plan specifies that `gate_eval_instrumentation.py` invokes `mine_outcome_corpus.py` as a subprocess (to avoid the `sys.exit()` on floor-check failure at line 381), but provides no fallback behavior for when the subprocess itself fails (non-zero exit). The `--no-refresh` flag is the only specified alternative, but it is opt-in. The plan is silent on what the harness does if the subprocess returns non-zero: does it abort, warn and continue with the stale corpus, or propagate the exit code?","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fa85c7f5b78c51b8f","impact":0.264,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section: 'Corpus acquisition (subprocess, not import)' and 'Scope' section CLI flags","norm_id":"nbd650f0c8977a0e0","priority":0.165,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["If git objects are partially pruned or the ticket store is incomplete, mine_outcome_corpus.py exits non-zero. The harness (without a specified fallback) may crash with an opaque error, leaving the operator unable to distinguish a miner failure from a harness bug.","In CI with --no-refresh not set, a transient subprocess failure silently prevents metrics emission without a documented recovery path."],"severity":"minor","suggested_fix":"Add: 'If the subprocess exits non-zero, the harness prints the subprocess stderr to its own stderr and exits non-zero (propagates the failure). Operators can bypass this with --no-refresh to use the committed corpus regardless.'","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"medium","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"low"}}},{"block_threshold":0.95,"blocking_enabled":false,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Acknowledge the RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY coupling in README.md and specify a sync mechanism (e.g., read the constant via a subprocess call to a small helper, embed a comment asserting the version it was pinned from, or add a CI check that the harness value matches the source constant) so recalibration doesn't silently diverge.","cohort":["T2","T5e","T7"],"criteria":["T5e"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["'The 0.5 floor is the codebase's own RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY (src/rebar/llm/plan_review/sidecar.py:299)'","The harness lives in non-package harnesses/ dir — plan says 'subprocess-by-path is also the clean invocation', implying no import of src/rebar constants","No mitigation for threshold drift is mentioned in Scope, README, or docs/plan-review-gate.md"],"finding":"The `has_strong_finding` predicate hardcodes `priority >= 0.5` (RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY from `sidecar.py:299`) directly in the harness, but the harness lives in a non-package directory and cannot import the constant. The plan does not acknowledge this coupling or provide a sync mechanism — if RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY is recalibrated in `src/rebar/`, the harness silently diverges and produces incorrect `UNKNOWABLE` classifications without any warning.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f886294e4fb8a627a","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"What section — `has_strong_finding` predicate; `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/gate_eval_instrumentation.py`","norm_id":"n061be37e42ee1c29","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY is updated in sidecar.py during a future calibration pass; the harness continues using 0.5 and silently misclassifies strong findings as UNKNOWABLE or vice versa, corrupting the trailing metrics without any visible error."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a comment block in gate_eval_instrumentation.py (and note in README.md) stating: 'RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY=0.5 is pinned from sidecar.py:299 as of <commit>; if recalibrated, update this constant and re-run --verify-repro.' Optionally add a CI assertion: `python -c \"from rebar.llm.plan_review.sidecar import RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY; assert RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY == 0.5, f'Harness out of sync: {RECALL_MIN_PRIORITY}'\"`.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"low","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"low","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"silent","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Add `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/README.md` to the Scope section's edit list, noting it should document the new `gate_eval_metrics.json` output file and its schema.","cohort":["G1G2"],"criteria":["G1G2"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/README.md exists and documents run artifacts","Plan scope: '--emit writes per-criterion metrics to docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json'","runs/README.md is not listed in the Scope section's file list"],"finding":"`docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/README.md` exists and documents the contents of the `runs/` directory, but the plan does not enumerate it as requiring an update when `gate_eval_metrics.json` is added as a new persistent output in that directory.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"fae1e8e010c935f2c","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section / docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/README.md","norm_id":"n1a57cc522afe802c","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["A future maintainer reads runs/README.md looking for a description of gate_eval_metrics.json and finds no entry, leading to confusion about the file's provenance and schema."],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"","tier":"LLM","validity":0.75,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"yes","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"no","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"yes","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac_unverifiable":"none","blast_radius":"local","debt_impact":"none","divergent_implementation":"none","dod_uncertifiable":"none","internal_conflict":"none","irreversible_without_rationale":"none","likelihood":"high","prod_impact":"none","reversibility":"easy","silent_vs_self_revealing":"self_revealing","undecomposed":"none","vague_directive":"none"}}},{"block_threshold":0.7,"blocking_enabled":true,"checklist_item":"- [ ] Address the existing `_atomic_write_jsonl` duplication (already copied between mine_outcome_corpus.py:389 and build_adjudication_corpus.py:190) before adding a third copy: either extract it to a shared `harness_utils.py` module in `harnesses/`, or explicitly call out in the plan that the new script will import it from one of the existing scripts (and document that as the intentional pattern).","cohort":["T1"],"criteria":["T1"],"decision":"advisory","drop_reason":"novelty","evidence":["mine_outcome_corpus.py:389-399 defines `_atomic_write_jsonl` as a private 12-line helper using tempfile.mkstemp + os.replace","build_adjudication_corpus.py:190-200 defines an identical `_atomic_write_jsonl` private helper — a confirmed duplication in the same directory","Plan AC2: '--emit writes per-criterion metrics to docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/runs/gate_eval_metrics.json' — the new script must write output atomically","Plan Scope is silent on reuse of the existing helper"],"finding":"The plan introduces a new harness script that will need to write output atomically (the --emit flag writes gate_eval_metrics.json), but two scripts already in the same harnesses/ directory (mine_outcome_corpus.py:389 and build_adjudication_corpus.py:190) each define an identical private `_atomic_write_jsonl` helper — prior art that has already been duplicated once. The plan is silent on whether the new script will copy this helper a third time or share it, making the copy-on-add pattern the default path of least resistance for an implementer.","group_criteria":null,"group_id":null,"id":"f5abffdcef3627907","impact":0.0,"is_primary":null,"location":"Scope section — `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/gate_eval_instrumentation.py`; also docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/mine_outcome_corpus.py:389 and build_adjudication_corpus.py:190","norm_id":"n4760f29400c4de55","priority":0.0,"reason":"default-advisory","scenarios":["Implementer adds a third copy of _atomic_write_jsonl in gate_eval_instrumentation.py, deepening an already-duplicated helper that future callers will also copy","A bug fix to the atomic-write logic (e.g., tempfile cleanup) must be applied to three separate copies"],"severity":"none","suggested_fix":"Add a single `docs/experiments/plan-review-gate/harnesses/harness_utils.py` containing `_atomic_write_jsonl` (and any other shared helpers like the common JSONL path constants), then have all three scripts import from it. The plan should name this module in the Scope section.","tier":"LLM","validity":0.625,"verification":{"binary":{"absence_confirmed_in_context":"yes","cited_reference_accurate":"yes","claims_absence":"yes","committed_work_relies_on_unbacked_claim":"na","evidence_entails_finding":"yes","impact_follows_necessarily":"no","is_verifiable":"yes","no_existing_mitigation":"yes","no_viable_alternative_explanation":"yes","path_reachable":"yes","respects_artifact_altitude":"no","severity_claim_justified":"no"},"severity_attributes":{"ac